          CSS 

       //first lines
<html>
    <head>
        <style>
        body {
            background: yellow;     /* red, blue, yellow, etc */
            color: red;            /* red, blue, yellow, etc */
            font-size: 20px;        /* 0px - 100px and beyond */
            font-weight: lighter;   /* lighter, normal, bold  */
            text-align: right;      /* left, center or right  */ 
            margin-top: 5px;        /* From 0px and upwards   */
        }        
        </style>
    </head>
    <body>
           Please accept our cookies!
    </body> 
</html>

SELECTOR- css works by targetting certain elements
on the page (html elements) and then styling them.

eg.
body {
    color: red;
}
within the curly braces you have 
PROPERTIES (color, font, margin)
and
VALUES (red, calibri, 2px)


             hex codes
 hexidecimal colours
 eg. saddlebrown is #8b4513,
      8b= red   45= green    13= blue   


                 Google clonesite
<html>
    <head> 
    external- <link rel="stylesheet" href="name of file and location"  
        <style>
        input {
            width: 400px;
        }
        img {
            width 350px;
        }

        </style>
    </head>
    <body>
        <img src="google.png" />
        <input type="text" />
    </body>
</html>

